# Qortfolio V2 Cursor Rules

## Project Structure & Methodology
- Follow the project structure as outlined in the development roadmap. Place new modules in their appropriate directories (e.g., `src/core/`, `src/data/`, `src/analytics/`, `src/dashboard/`).
- Use Agile development with weekly sprints and clear handoff documentation between phases and contributors.
- All code must be tested with >90% coverage, especially for core utilities and critical calculations.

## Critical Bugs & Fixes
- **Time-to-maturity calculation must use the correct formula:**
  - `time_diff.total_seconds() / (365.25 * 24 * 3600)`
  - Do NOT use the legacy formula: `time_diff.total_seconds() / 31536000 * 365`
- Track and prioritize legacy bugs (e.g., RNN/LSTM/GRU shape mismatches, model loading failures, dashboard crashes) as per the status tracker.
- Document all bug fixes in handoff notes, including test results and configuration decisions.

## Feature Implementation
- **Options Analytics Module (Phase 1 Priority):**
  - Real-time options data collection from Deribit (BTC/ETH).
  - Black-Scholes pricing engine with Greeks (Delta, Gamma, Theta, Vega, Rho).
  - Gamma exposure calculations at both portfolio and position levels.
  - Options chain analysis and real-time updates.
- **Volatility Analysis Module:**
  - yfinance integration for top cryptocurrencies.
  - Statistical and ML-based volatility analysis (MLP, RNN, LSTM, GRU).
  - Volatility surfaces and statistical dashboards.
- **Dashboard Module:**
  - Streamlit-based UI.
  - Dedicated pages for options analytics, volatility surfaces, and statistical analysis.
  - Real-time data updates and visualizations.

## Data Handling & Validation
- Comprehensive error handling is required for all data collectors and integrations.
- Data validation must be performed after collection, with invalid entries removed and results logged.
- Configuration management should use YAML files for crypto mappings and API settings, with environment variable support.

## Documentation & Handoff
- Document all major decisions (e.g., configuration, bug fixes, feature implementations) in the appropriate markdown files.
- Update the status tracker as tasks are completed or bugs are fixed.
- Acceptance criteria for each phase/task must be clearly checked off before moving to the next.
